Still, throwing education into the maelstrom of American class just makes
the whole thing more complicated. And then on top of that, there=E2=80=99s
occupation. Karl Marx conceived of class as being closely tied to what you
do for a living =E2=80=94 the proletariat were wage-earning laborers, the p=
etit
